# Tokens

Tokens are the material of Pathogen. They keep small decisions consistent enough that the interface feels quiet, precise, accessible, compact, and trustworthy across components and host apps.

Write shared components in terms of **roles** (`--pvc-color-accent-solid`), not palette stops (`primary-700`). Palette stops can change. Roles describe intent.

## Host Theme Overrides

| Variable | Pathogen default | Host apps |
|----------|------------------|-----------|
| `--color-primary-*` | Blue | Brand / action colour (IRIDA: green) |
| `--color-neutral-*` | Slate, exposed as `neutral-*` | Leave as-is unless theming the whole neutral system |
| `--font-sans` | Inter stack | Optional product font |
| `--font-mono` | System mono | Code and IDs |

Use `neutral-*` in components, not raw `slate-*`. `neutral` is the public name; slate is the implementation.

## Token Layers

```text
Palette
  primary, neutral, status hues
    ↓
Semantic roles
  --pvc-color-*, --type-*, --pvc-radius-*, motion
    ↓
Component-scoped tokens
  data grid internals, tooltip placement
```

Grid and tooltip tokens are internal. Do not override them from host apps unless the host is intentionally theming the whole component.

## Colour Roles

Swatches show Pathogen defaults. Hosts remap accent through `--color-primary-*`.

