### Choosing Accent And Danger Tokens

| Situation | Tokens |
|-----------|--------|
| Text, borders, outline/ghost on a surface | `accent`, `accent-strong` |
| Filled primary button | `accent-solid`, `accent-solid-hover` |
| Outline/ghost destructive | `danger-strong`, `danger` |
| Filled destructive | `danger-solid`, `danger-solid-hover` |

In dark mode, accent text and borders lighten for contrast. Solid button fills stay saturated so action colour still feels deliberate. Focus is a separate role; the target is `primary-500` in both modes so focus does not collapse into accent.

## Type Scale

```css
--type-meta: 0.75rem;      /* 12px */
--type-control: 0.875rem;  /* 14px */
--type-body: 1rem;         /* 16px */
--type-callout: 1.125rem;  /* 18px */
--type-section: 1.25rem;   /* 20px */
--type-title: 1.5rem;      /* 24px */
--type-page: 2rem;         /* 32px */
```

| Token | px | Used by |
|-------|----|---------|
| `--type-meta` | 12 | Hints, `Supporting` (`size: :meta`), heading-group metadata |
| `--type-control` | 14 | Labels, buttons, `Supporting` (default), inline code |
| `--type-body` | 16 | Body text, lists, `Heading` level 6 |
| `--type-callout` | 18 | `Callout`, `Heading` levels 4–5 |
| `--type-section` | 20 | Section titles, `Lead`, `Heading` level 3 |
| `--type-title` | 24 | `Heading` level 2 |
| `--type-page` | 32 | Page titles, `Heading` level 1 |

Components consume these through `text-[length:var(--type-*)]` utilities. The scale is role-based, not a strict mathematical ratio. Each step should be the smallest jump that clearly changes hierarchy.

## Spacing

Spacing uses the 4px Tailwind rhythm.

| px | Class | Good for |
|----|-------|----------|
| 4 | `1` | Tight padding |
| 8 | `2` | Control internals |
| 12 | `3` | Radio rows |
| 16 | `4` | Form gaps |
| 24 | `6` | Sections |
| 32 | `8` | Major regions |

Do not tokenise spacing unless a repeated component pattern needs a named value.

## Radius

```css
--pvc-radius-control-sm: 0.125rem; /* 2px */
--pvc-radius-control: 0.25rem;     /* 4px */
--pvc-radius-action: 0.375rem;     /* 6px */
--pvc-radius-panel: 0.5rem;        /* 8px */
```

Use the radius that matches the role. Prefer `rounded-[var(--pvc-radius-action)]` over guessing `rounded-md` when the component job is known.

## Elevation

```css
--pvc-shadow-none: none;
--pvc-shadow-overlay: 0 1px 3px oklch(0 0 0 / 0.2);
```

Base product surfaces stay flat. Overlays get the small shadow because they float above the work.

## Motion

```css
--pvc-duration-fast: 120ms;
--pvc-duration-default: 160ms;
--pvc-duration-overlay: 200ms;
```

Use colour, border, background, and opacity transitions before movement. Honour `prefers-reduced-motion`.

## Component-Specific Tokens

**Data grid** — `--pvc-data-grid-*` controls grid borders, cell padding, and body background. These tokens are internal to the grid.

**Tooltip** — `--pvc-tooltip-origin` controls placement. Tooltip fill uses `neutral-950`; that is overlay territory, not page canvas.

## Where Components Are Today

| Component | Semantic colour | Radius tokens | Type tokens |
|-----------|-----------------|---------------|-------------|
| `Button` | Yes | `--pvc-radius-action` | via `text-sm` |
| `CopyableValue` | Yes | `--pvc-radius-action` | `--type-meta` |
| `Typography` | Yes | Tailwind | `--type-*` |
| `Link`, `Tabs`, `Form` | Partial | Mixed | `text-sm` labels |
| `DataGrid` | Grid-scoped | `rounded-lg` ~= panel | - |
| `Tooltip` | Hard-coded | `rounded-lg` | - |

New work should follow `Button`.

